Spritz Cookies

Ingredients (Serves 2 | Makes ~18 cookies)

Cookie Dough
	•	1/2 cup (113 g) unsalted butter
	•	1/2 cup (100 g) granulated sugar
	•	1 large egg yolk
	•	1 1/10 cups (140 g) all-purpose flour
	•	1 teaspoon vanilla extract
	•	1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt

⸻

Method
	1.	Heat Oven
Preheat to 350°F (175°C). Position rack in the center. Use an ungreased baking sheet.
	2.	Brown Butter
Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until milk solids turn golden brown and smell nutty.
Transfer to a bowl and cool 5 minutes (warm, not hot).
	3.	Cream Butter & Sugar
Beat browned butter and sugar until pale and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
	4.	Add Yolks & Flavoring
Mix in egg yolk, vanilla, and salt until smooth and fully emulsified.
	5.	Incorporate Flour
Mix in flour on low speed just until combined. Dough should be soft but pipeable.
Rest 10 minutes.
	6.	Press Cookies
Load dough into a cookie press (or piping bag with star tip). Press directly onto baking sheet with even spacing.
	7.	Bake
Bake 12–15 minutes, until edges are lightly golden and centers remain pale.
	8.	Cool Slightly
Rest 5 minutes on tray, then transfer to a rack. Serve warm or fully cooled.

⸻

Optional Enhancements
	•	Add citrus zest (lemon or orange) to the dough
	•	Dip half of each cookie in melted dark chocolate
	•	Sprinkle with sanding sugar before baking for crunch
	•	Chill dough briefly if shapes lose definition